FIGS. 4A to 4C illustrates a basic driving principle of an EOC-LCD according to a second embodiment of the present invention;


FIG. 5 is a plan view of an electrode formed in a pixel unit in an EOC-LCD according to a third embodiment of the present invention;


FIG. 6, is a plan view of an electrode formed in a pixel unit in an EOC-LCD according to a fourth embodiment of the present invention;


FIGS. 7 to 17 are,graphical illustrations of a viewing angle of an EOC-LCD according to an embodiment of the present invention; and


FIG. 18 is a graphical illustration of electro-optical characteristics in an EOC-LCD according to an embodiment of the present invention.
